description._content: Creator: E. S. Watson Location: Queensland, Australia Description: Caption: 1915--"Lest we forget"--1931. Illustration of a solitary Australian soldier leaning on his upturned rifle, on a ridge overlooking a small cove, just before sunrise. A number of crosses rise out of the ground in the distance. This is an ANZAC day memorial cover and the cove is presumed to be Gallipoli.
